<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-converting-tablespoons-to-cups-and-v=
ice-versa">Converting Tablespoons to Cups and Vice Versa</h2>



<p><strong>The table below shows a conversion of tablespoons to cup and vic=
e versa:</strong></p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>TABLESPOON</=
strong></td><td><strong>CUP</strong></td></tr><tr><td>2 tablespoons</td><td=
>1/8 cup</td></tr><tr><td>4 tablespoons</td><td>1/4 cup</td></tr><tr><td>5 =
1/3 tablespoons</td><td>1/3 cup</td></tr><tr><td>8 tablespoons</td><td>1/2 =
cup</td></tr><tr><td>12 tablespoons</td><td>3/4 cup</td></tr><tr><td>16 tab=
lespoons</td><td>1 cup</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class=3D"wp-ele=
ment-caption">Source: <a href=3D"https://www.exploratorium.edu/food/measure=
ments" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">Exploratorium.edu</a><=
/figcaption></figure>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">=F0=9F=92=A1Tip:</h3>



<p><em>The table is based on liquid volume equivalents. If you want to use =
the table above for dry measures (e.g. a tablespoon of flour) in cooking it=
 does work. However, it=E2=80=99s not completely accurate. If you want to b=
e totally certain, can also consider measuring dry ingredients by weight in=
stead. </em></p>



<p>Another helpful tool is<a href=3D"https://samsungfood.com/blog/cups-to-g=
rams-conversion/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener"> <strong>Cu=
ps to Grams Conversion</strong></a>. A cups to grams conversion table is a =
helpful tool for converting measurements from cups to grams, based on the r=
equirements of your recipe.&nbsp;If you=E2=80=99re using dry ingredients or=
 want to be really precise in your measurements, weight is often a better i=
ndicator than volume (like cups or tablespoons). </p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-tablespoons-to-cups">Tablespoons to =
Cups:</h3>



<p>To convert from tablespoons to cups, simply divide the number of tablesp=
oons by 16. This is because there are 16 tablespoons in a cup. For instance=
, if you have 32 tablespoons, divide 32 by 16 to get 2 cups.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-cups-to-tablespoons">Cups to Tablesp=
oons:</h3>



<p>To convert from cups to tablespoons, multiply the number of cups by 16. =
For example, if you have 1.5 cups, multiply 1.5 by 16 to get 24 tablespoons=
.</p>



